The paper deals with active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that involves selecting the most informative samples to label. The paper also discusses algorithms for selecting which model to probe next, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem formulation involves a fixed budget of probes, which suggests a focus on resource allocation and optimization, placing the paper in the subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the empirical performance of various algorithms, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
